dialogStrings:
“The master is an experienced
climber, you know.”{PAUSE}“I've heard that he knows every
corner of that Great Glacier!”

“Grandma,
don't sleep so close to the fire!”

“Grandma's been sick for a while
and doesn't have much energy…”

“My husband left 20 years ago
and still hasn't come back.”{PAUSE}“He should at least be at the foot
of Gaea's Cliff.
It's marked with a check on the map…”

“…cough…cough…
I've been living in this town for 60 years.
And I STILL caught a cold…”{PAUSE}“I heard there's a doctor
on a Southern island somewhere.
I sure wish he'd come here…cough…cough…”

“It's nearly impossible to reach
the Northern limits without a map.”{PAUSE}“If you're thinkin' 'bout going
to the Northern limits,
you'd better take that map on the wall.”

“What nerve!
You already tore down the map.”

“I'm thinkin' 'bout
taking that hill on my skis.”

“It's the first time that the temperature
has dipped this low, this fast…”{PAUSE}“There's also that mysterious light
at the Northern limits, too.
Does this mean
it's the end of the world?”
